{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix uninitialized measurements in LTE UE emulation mode\n\n### Summary\nThe `lte_ue_measurements_emul()` function in the LTE UE PHY layer was not properly initializing measurement values when running in emulation mode. This caused unpredictable behavior when higher layers attempted to access these measurements.\n\nThe function was previously just a stub that logged a message but didn't populate the measurements structure. This fix implements proper measurement initialization with reasonable default values for emulation mode.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_ESTIMATION/lte_ue_measurements.c`: Replaced stub implementation with proper measurement initialization\n- Fixed parameter name mismatch between header and implementation (subframe -> last_slot)\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running LTE UE in emulation mode with channel estimation enabled, the UE would exhibit inconsistent behavior due to uninitialized measurement values. Symptoms included:\n- Random fluctuations in reported RSRP/RSRQ values\n- Incorrect CQI reporting affecting scheduling decisions\n- Potential segfaults when accessing uninitialized measurement arrays\n\nThe issue can be reproduced by running the LTE UE simulator with `--emul` flag and monitoring the measurement reports through the RRC interface.\n"
}